<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9501] Promote Standby tasks to active tasks without closing them</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9501</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The purpose of StandbyTasks in Kafka Streams is fast failover. However, atm we close StandbyTasks (and create a new active task) if they are promoted to active.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While this works ok for persistent state stores, it renders hot standbys for in-memory state stores useless, because we drop the in-memory state when we close the StandbyTask and thus the new active tasks needs to reread the changelog topic to recreate the in-memory state.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, we should promote StandbyTasks to active tasks without closing them. This will not only fix the issue for in-memory stores, but will make rebalancing faster for persistent state stores, too, because closing and reopening RocksDB has significant overhead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
